description: Yes, it's Ladies' Only Night for this issue! Goody two-shoes superheroine Tomorrow Girl and her rival, the danger-seeking, bona fide teenage ninja girl Sora Wakahishi, try to work together to cheer up a heartbroken Nanashi, who's just out of the hospital, with a girls' night on the town! But what can they do when repentant former assassin Suzume unleashes all her bloodlust and rage during the outing? Girls will be girls!
name: Girls' Night Out

description:
It's the issue BEFORE issue 150!

Five hundred years ago, a man known only as Yuudai, "the great hero," created the art of ninjitsu. Recently reincarnated, he has amassed an elite force bent on eliminating all inferior ninja. Determined to draw out Ricky Feeple and test his mettle, Yuudai has captured several of Ricky's friends. Sure enough, a lone man comes charging to their aid, determined to make Yuudai pay for what he's done. Yes, it's...Tetsuo to the rescue?!
name: The King is Dead

description:
It is a comic book rule: Whenever a series hits a multiple of 25, it's time to celebrate. This is especially true when the issue also marks a book's 20th anniversary! Everyone at Antarctic Press wants to celebrate, so we're all contributing to this one! Fred Perry (Gold Digger), David Hutchison (Oz: The Manga), Rod Espinosa (DinoWars), Joe Wight (Twilight X) and the original creator himself, Ben Dunn, (Ninja High School, obviously) all conspire on a multitude of short stories that showcase the crazy town of Quagmire U.S.A. Characters old and new get to run around fighting crime, visit the zoo, play music, travel to Japan, cast magic spells, explore outer space, get drunk, play dress-up, and more!

This fun-packed, stand-alone, extra-special issue is the ultimate introduction to the world of Ninja High School, a perfect entry point for anyone who ever wondered why the adventures of these plucky ninja teens have been a fan favorite and an Antarctic Press staple for over two decades!

The three covers on the right are:

1) The standard cover.

2) A "Sketch Edition" cover. (Each is individually drawn.)

3) A "Crew Sign" cover. (Each is individually signed.)
name: Tales of Quagmire

description:
The groundbreaking stories that set the standard for an entire era of mystical adventure! Aided and abetted by lover Clea and man-servant Wong, the newly minted Sorcerer Supreme takes on Demons, the Dread Dormammu, Dracula, the Defenders, Deathand Doctor Strange!? Plus: Planet Earth is no more! The Master of the Mystic Arts fights alone against Eternity, as the world stands on the brink of oblivion! Also featuring the return of the Ancient One and the mind-boggling 'Creator Chronicles,' and guest-starring Nighthawk!

Collecting DOCTOR STRANGE #1-29 and ANNUAL #1, and TOMB OF DRACULA #44-45.
name: Volume 3

description: See for yourself how the Marvel Age of Heroes began as one of comicdom's coolest chroniclers follows the FF, Spider-Man, the X-Men, Daredevil and others from origins into adventure! Recounting the first appearances of Marvel's greatest menaces—including Doctor Octopus, Doctor Doom, Magneto and Loki! The awakening of the Sub-Mariner and Captain America! Ancient enigmas, wartime wonders and more from the first years of the House of Ideas! Collecting MARVEL SAGA #1-12
name: Volume 1

description:
After an ancient truce existing between humankind and the invisible realm of the fantastic is broken, hell on earth is ready to erupt. A ruthless leader who treads the world above and the one below defies his bloodline and awakens an unstoppable army of creatures. Now, it's up to the planet's toughest, roughest superhero to battle the merciless dictator and his marauders. He may be red. He may be horned. He may be misunderstood. But when you need the job done right, it's time to call Hellboy.

Along with his expanding team in the Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense-pyrotechnic girlfriend Liz Sherman, aquatic empath Abe Sapien, and protoplasmic mystic Johann--the B.P.R.D. will travel between the surface strata and the unseen magical one, where creatures of fantasy become corporeal. And Hellboy, a creature of two worlds, who's accepted by neither, must choose between the life he knows and an unknown destiny that beckons him.
name: Movie Adaptation

description:
In "The Judgment Bell," written by Jim Pascoe (Kim Possible, Buffy the Vampire Slayer) and drawn by Rick Lacy (Venture Brothers), a figure from Dr. Broom's past wreaks havoc on the children of a small Polish village. And in a backup story written and drawn by Hellboy Animated creator Tad Stones, a young Hellboy is once again stirred to heroism by the radio adventures of Lobster Johnson.

With a cover by Eisner award-winning Goon creator Eric Powell and an original pinup by Hellboy creator Mike Mignola, this book is the perfect bridge between the comics and cartoon worlds of the World's Greatest Paranormal Detective.
name: The Judgment Bell; The Menace Of The Mechanical Monster

description: The Lobster returns for the gripping conclusion to The Iron Prometheus, where he battles a fearsome criminal mastermind and Nazis on the Jersey Shore, in an attempt to waylay a mysterious prophecy.

The Monaghan's have a problem -- faeries have stolen their baby. Tam O'Clannie's problem is he wants a Christian burial, and he's already getting pretty ripe. Hellboy has more than his share of problems with border goblins, dead men, and war monsters, as he tries to make everyone happy in one night, roaming the Irish landscape looking for a Christian graveyard and finding only pagan monstrosities. The complete story, "The Corpse," the first part of which was serialized in Advance Comics, concludes here with an all-new back-up, "The Iron Shoes," in which Hellboy enters a battered, medieval tower to take on a footnote from Irish folklore.
name: The Corpse; The Iron Shoes

volume.name: Hellboy: The Corpse And The Iron Shoes

description: Following Eve, a dangerously seductive woman on the edge of her sanity, PHERONE weaves a dark storyline filled with espionage, mystery and suspense. Armed with a killer body and a killer's mind, the femme fatale must hunt down clues to rediscover her own troubled past, bringing violence and danger to anyone who crosses her path.
Features an Andy Panda story with an older Charlie Chicken (see #79) by John Stanley
An Andy Panda and Charlie Chicken story by John Stanley appears here.

Under Circes spell, Hippolyta has been made to believe that someone else's life is actually her own, and even Wonder Woman's lasso of truth is unable to break the evil sorceress spell over her mother. Will Diana, newly returned to Earth from Olympus, lose her mother altogether just as she begins her life among mankind?
name: The Loss

description: This month: Joe's Dope - A Formula For Better Tyre Care.

A dark god, released by the destruction of the planet Krypton, finds her way to Earth to extinguish the "last flame" of Krypton's fire.  Blanketing the whole of the Earth in the snows of a new Ice Age--her mythological power--she intends to bring the last son of Krypton to the fore.  When she discovers he bears a similar "beauty" to Rao--originator of the house of El and another god of Krypton whom she intended to trap in marriage--she changes her plans.  Instead of killing Superman, she now intends to wed him.
However, as she's a stranger to this part of the galaxy, she is at a disadvantage when facing the things that make a Superman out of Kal-El.  Sadly, she underestimates the love of Lois Lane, the hatred of Lex Luthor and the power of Sol, Earth's yellow sun.
name: Superman: The Last God of Krypton

volume.name: Superman: The Last God of Krypton

description: The Fallen has been released at long last and now plans to use the Sun-harvester to destroy the sun and convert it into energon. The Autobots and Decepticons then begin their final battle. The humans call the pentagon for support but their message does not get across and the constructicons combine to form Devastator. The Decepticons attempt to use Sam's parents to threaten him to give them the Matrix, but with the help of Bumblebee, his parents are saved. Sam, believing he is needed, goes to fight with the Autobots. Devastator in the meantime begins to rip apart the top of a pyramid to reveal the Sun-Harvester hidden underneath it. While the military helps with the battle against the Decepticons, Sam seeks Optimus Prime and with Jetfire's help he makes it to him and as he does, he meets the dynasty of Primes in a vision and obtains the Matrix of Leadership which is then used to revive Optimus Prime. However, the Fallen then takes the matrix and tries to activate the Sun Harvester. The military get back up and take out Devastator while Optimus heads for a final battle with the Fallen. Megatron interferes, believing that the Fallen will give him power, but Optimus tells him that he was lied to as Primes are born - not made - and proceeds to finish off the Fallen who begs Megatron to help him with the empty promise of making him a God which Megatron does not fall for.The symbols Sam once saw are now with Optimus along with all the history of Cybertron's past. As the humans and Autobots then plan to go and discover their connections from the past, Megatron begins rebuilding a new army...
name: Part 4

volume.name: Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen - Official Movie Adaptation

description: Dave Sim's Archives File Drawer #1 (1972-1979) provides the raw material for Cerebus Archive, the new light-hearted bi-monthly series from Cerebus creator Dave Sim, covering his career from 1972 to the present! It's a mortified (but tongue-in-cheek) look back by Dave Sim at the first prototype drawings of his earliest cartoon creations, The Beavers, along with his first professionally published comic-book story 'Cry of the White Wolf' (art by Stan Connerty), complete in this issue! In addition to Sim's commentary, you'll also find letters from Gene Day the year before he was accepted at Marvel Comics, a rejection letter from Gray Morrow, and a 1975 reproduction from the only comic book to feature - in one issue - the work of John Byrne, Gene Day, Frank Cirocco and Dave Sim. With six issues 'in the can' - and the creation of Cerebus as a cartoon mascot for a sword-and-sorcery/fantasy fanzine still a year away... Cerebus Archive might turn out to be Dave Sim's next 300-issue limited series! Available in two cover versions: 'Cry of the White Aardvark' or a Cerebus #1 Zombie Variant!
name: Cry Of The White Aardvark

description: It's the crossover to end all crossovers! The Mask takes a whirlwind tour of the Dark Horse Heroes' universe, and he starts by butting heads with Hero Zero! Can Hero Zero take the punishment? Will the Mask survive a mystical onslaught of King Tiger? The world of the Dark Horse Heroes may never be the same again.

The Mask's arrival in Steel Harbor turns out to be more fun than a barrel of greased weasels! At least, that's what The Mask thinks. The Machine and Barb Wire aren't so sure, especially after Big-Head commits a major faux paus in front of Barb. Steel Harbor just might have to be renamed "shrapnelville," unless King Tiger and Dr. Snider can get to General Blaire, the man behind The Mask, before Barb does!

Arcadia has always been a dark and gritty town. But not even its street-smart citizens are ready for The Mask! If Ghost, X, and King Tiger can't bring him down, Arcadia's gonna have more grit and darkness than it knows what to do with!

The Mask has toughed out a tangle with Barb Wire and The Machine in Steel Harbor and given X and Ghost a good going-over in Arcadia. Next stop -- Golden City! The place is a utopia to some, and Tartarus to others. But to The Mask, it's just the last stop on his way home from a mayhem-filled tour!

Ripped from today's headlines, the End War comes to its violent climax. Kazi has found a way to kill The Man Who Cannot Die, and with The Phantom out of commission, who will put an end to The Cleansing? Plus, the serialized Phantom prose back-ups continue.
name: End War, Part 3

description: Our thrilling Terminator series comes to a time-crossing conclusion! Writer Simon Furman and artist Lui Antonio provide unparalleled action and excitement as the Dire Wolf and T-Infinity clash and humanity strikes a deadly blow against Skynet which opens a slight ray of hope for humanity for the first time in a very long time.

Featuring CAPTAIN AMERICA, the Sentinel of Liberty, in the then & now! In the Now, he faces the hyper-technological might of Hydra! In the then, he battles the disgusting (and frankly, ugly) menace of P.R.O.D.O.K.!
name: Web Of Deceit; If This Be P.R.O.D.O.K.

description: This softcover collection gathers not only issues #1-3 of the hilariously fucky porn parody series, but also an all-new, eight page, full-color tale created just for this volume, in which Boffy attends a paranormal convention and meets Bleed the Vampire Skewer, Vampire Humper D, and more!
name: Boffy the Vampire Layer

description:
A journalist working as a police reporter goes undercover as a fashion photographer. It seems that rich elderly gentlemen are hiring supermodels at premium prices to perform sex acts privately for them. Anything goes in these clandestine meetings. Enter Luna.... the most beautiful supermodel of them all. The journalist has a session with Luna and he becomes obsessed with her natural beauty. In the end the reporter gets his story, but will he get Luna? Beautifully painted full-color artwork from Greece. 80 pages.

Back Blurb

Models, naked bodies and mature gentlemen willing to pay and watch. The fashion world, the glamorous pages of magazines and the shocking revelations of pop tabloids. Aris Sartas is once again on the streets. The reporter of The Journal in search of front page news. He knows love for money but confuses police reporting with fashion editorials. Fashion, media, models. Night and day. The trafficking of love. Known names of the Athenian society and beautiful girls with exotic names. Luna, Lu to her friends. She stirs the city's nightlife. She smiles on the cover of magazines. At nights she strips for art lovers. And for Sartas.

Pink Sniper is filled with half animal people, flying sci-fi vehicles, loose women, and Haruana's giant breasts. Creator Kengo Yonekura's beautiful, lush art brings to life this wild tale of lust, sex, and strangeness. A full-length manga graphic novel in traditional right-to-left format!
